.TH manta-gen-man 1  "gen-man " 
.SH NAME
manta\-gen\-man \- Generate and install manta man pages
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBmanta gen\-man\fR [\fB\-p\fR|\fB\-\-path\fR] [\fB\-o\fR|\fB\-\-output\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Generate one man\-page (`.1`) per subcommand from the running binary\*(Aqs clap tree and write them into the target directory.
.PP
Defaults to `$XDG_DATA_HOME/man/man1` (i.e. `~/.local/share/man/man1`) when `\-\-path` is omitted. The directory is created if it doesn\*(Aqt exist.
.PP
After install, configure your shell so `man` finds the new location — on Linux this directory is searched by default; on macOS you may need `export MANPATH="$HOME/.local/share/man:$MANPATH"`.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-p\fR, \fB\-\-path\fR \fI<PATH>\fR
Directory to write the `.1` files into (defaults to $XDG_DATA_HOME/man/man1)
.TP
\fB\-o\fR, \fB\-\-output\fR \fI<FORMAT>\fR [default: table]
Output format
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
table
.IP \(bu 2
json
.RE
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
